Type Casting:
-Type Casting is converting the type of data from one type of data to another one. 

We have 2 types of type casting:
	1. -Explicit/Narrowing/Manual
	2. - Implicit/widening/automatic
	
	When we go from a bigger data type to a smaller one : Explicit/narrowing/manual
	When we go from a smaller data type to a larger one : Implicit/widening/automatic
	
	1. Byte (8)
	2. Short (16), Char(16)
	3. Int (32)
	4. Long (64)
	5. Float (32)	3222 3.2*1000000000000= 3.2E12
	6. Double (64)
	
	Byte->short->char->int->long->float->double
	
	Why we need type casting?
	 - When we are working in teams we might nneed to convert data from different data types.
	 - When we are working with math sometimes we need to get rid of decimal part as we are only interested in the non-decimal part.
	 
	What is the syntax?
	Explicit/narrowing/manual
		int box=1000;
		byte box2=(byte) box;
	
	Implicit/widening/automatic
	
		short box1=250;
		int box ;	
		
